service.name: General Practice Rural Incentive Programme
service.description: The General Practice Rural Incentive Programme aims to encourage medical practitioners to relocate to and practice in rural and remote communities and to promote careers in rural medicine. It combines two previously separate retention incentive programs available to general practitioners (GPs) and Registrars, and provides a new relocation grant.
